{
  "texts": [
    "Together with Lemmas 7.3 and 7.4 this implies that ψ = ω X e • Ad[V], as required.",
    "□ Proof of Proposition 7.2: It follows from the previous Lemma that any state ψ, corresponding under the representation π X C to a unit vector in H of the form |Ψ⟩ = π 1 (O)|Ω⟩ for some O ∈ A loc, is a vector state for the GNS representation π X e. Indeed, a representing vector is given by π X e (V) |Ω X e ⟩ where |Ω X e ⟩ denotes the cyclic vector of the GNS representation corresponding to the state ω X e, and V ∈ A is the unitary granted by Theorem 7.8.",
    "In particular, any such ψ is a pure state.",
    "Since π 1 (A loc) |Ω⟩ is dense in H, it follows that π X C is irreducible.",
    "By Lemma 7.1 the state ω X e is a vector state for both irreducible representations π X C and π X e, so we conclude that π X C ≃ u.e."
  ]
}